OL,3,CHS2: Spiralling costs, slower trains,
OL,4,Cless than half the size - what went
OL,5,Cwrong?
OL,7,FThe project had initially been set for
OL,8,Fa maiden voyage as early as 2026.
OL,10,FLast year, the transport secretary
OL,11,Fconfirmed this delay, saying she saw
OL,12,F"no route by which trains can be
OL,13,Frunning by 2033 as planned".
OL,15,FPointing to a "litany of failure" in
OL,16,Fthe HS2 project and its management,
OL,17,FAlexander described an "appalling
OL,18,Fmess", saying: "Billions of pounds of
OL,19,Ftaxpayers' money has been wasted by
OL,20,Fconstant scope changes, ineffective
OL,21,Fcontracts and bad management."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G22/23
